"""
Company-Opportunity Matching Pipeline (v3 — analyst-grade)
===========================================================

Refined architecture beyond the 8-step flowchart, applying matching-system
best practices and prompt-engineering techniques that actually move output
quality on this kind of task.

What changed from v2
--------------------
1. Embedding model bumped to `text-embedding-3-large` (3072-dim).
   ada-002 is older; 3-large is materially better on industrial/business
   text and roughly the same price.
2. Hybrid retrieval: dense embedding + BM25 sparse score, blended.
   Dense catches semantics ("desalination" ↔ "membrane filtration"),
   sparse catches exact product/segment names ("Pentacam", "5G NR antenna").
3. Three-signal scoring: profile_similarity, product_similarity, sparse_score.
4. Richer GPT input: full company profile (no aggressive truncation), full
   opportunity description, opportunity highlights/demand drivers/materials,
   plus the structured-extracted entity lists.
5. Few-shot examples in the prompt — one strong-Yes, one principled-No —
   to anchor tone, specificity, and structure.
6. New output fields demanded by users:
     match_value      0-100 quantitative quality score from GPT
     match_confidence Low | Medium | High
     ai_decision      Yes | No        (kept)
     ai_explanation   investment-memo paragraph (kept, sharpened)
     ai_insight       non-obvious strategic angle (kept)
     suggested_plan   3 sequenced concrete steps (kept, sharpened)
     match_reason     3 evidence-cited reasons (kept)
7. GPT decision happens on EVERY pair — no stub rows. Match-path label
   (sector_overlap | soft_match | weak_overlap) is passed to the model
   so it can calibrate, not skip.

Output: Output/business_grade_company_opportunity_matches.xlsx
Schema (20 columns):
  id, companyId, opportunityId, company_name, opportunity_name,
  company_sector, opportunity_sector,
  sector_similarity, profile_similarity, product_similarity, sparse_score,
  ai_score, ai_decision, match_value, match_confidence, final_score,
  ai_explanation, rank, ai_insight, suggested_plan, match_reason

final_score formula (kept compatible with reference MatchingOutput.csv):
  final_score = 0.30 * ai_score + 0.30 * profile_similarity + 0.40 * product_similarity
"""

